                  </hi>.—<hi rend="italic">He was further charged with a former conviction in September</hi>, 1861; <hi rend="italic">to which he</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">PLEADED GUILTY</hi>.**—<hi rend="italic">
The Mint authorities stated that he had been repeatedly in custody, and had been sentenced to nine months, one year, and two years, and that he boasted that he could not be set to hard labour, in consequence of a deformity of his foot
